<DOC><DOCNO> AP890309-0067 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-09-89 0919EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Saudi-Afghanistan     03-09 0186</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Saudi-Afghanistan,0190</SECOND><HEAD>Saudi Arabia Recognizes Afghan Guerrilla Government</HEAD><DATELINE>RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Saudi Arabia today became the firstcountry to officially recognize the Afghan guerrillagovernment-in-exile.   Saudi Arabia did so because the members of thegovernment-in-exile were chosen freely by the Moslem guerrillaleaders, the official Saudi Press Agency quoted a Foreign Ministrystatement as saying.   Saudi Arabia, home of Islam's holiest shrines, carriesconsiderable weight in the Moslem world. The oil-rich kingdom hasgiven the Moslem guerrillas considerable support in their struggleagainst the Afghan government and the Soviet army, which withdrewlast month after nine years of fighting.   The United States and Pakistan also supplied the anti-communistforces with weapons and funding during the Soviet intervention.   Saudi Arabia will host a meeting of foreign ministers from the46-member Islamic Conference organization later this month. Amongother issues the conference will discuss recognizing the Afghanguerrilla's government-in-exile, which was proclaimed in Pakistan onFeb. 24.   The president of the guerrilla government, Sibghatullah Mojaddidion Wednesday called on the United Nations and the Islamic Conferenceorganization to recognize the new leaderhsip of the insurgency.</TEXT></DOC>